        textArea6.setCursor(new java.awt.Cursor(java.awt.Cursor.DEFAULT_CURSOR));
        textArea6.setEditable(false);
        textArea6.setFont(new java.awt.Font("Tahoma", 0, 12)); // NOI18N
        textArea6.setForeground(new java.awt.Color(51, 51, 51));
        textArea6.setRows(6);
        textArea6.setText("There are hundreds of graduates produced by NSBM in the field of Management Information Systems and all the graduates are working in large and reputed Software Development Companies and leading banks in Srilanka.\nNSBM is having more than 15 Years maturity (Including the experience at NIBM) in awarding degrees in Information Systems.\nAnother important fact in this degree program is students are more exposed into good job opportunities while they are completing the internship in the third year of the academic calendar.\nFinding interns is not a big challenge to NSBM students as they are well developed in skills and professionally groomed during the first two academic years.\nNSBM take the responsibility of placing students in internships and most of the time these students get the employment in the same place as their performance are up to the industry standard.\n\nYEAR 1\nFull Time\n\nIntroduction to Computer Science\nMathematics for Computing\nC Language and Data Structures\nComputer Organization\nOOP with C++\nBusiness Information Systems\nDatabase Management Systems\nProgramming in JAVA\nSystem Software\nVisual Basic .Net Programming\nInternet Programming\nSystem Analysis and Design\nSoft Skills\nSystem Design Project\nYEAR 2\nFull TIme\n\nManagement Practices\nSoftware Engineering\nData Structures & Algorithms\nBusiness Statistics for Information Technology\nAdvance Database Management Systems\nObject Oriented Programming and Design 1\nAgile Software Development Methodologies\nOperational Research\nObject Oriented Programming and Design II\nDistributed Processing\nData Warehousing and Data Mining\nComputer Networking\nSoft Skills\nSystem Design Project\nYEAR 3\nPart Time\n\nIndustrial Training\nManagement Information Systems\nDatabase and Information Resource Management\nIT Project Management\nFundamentals of E- Business\nComputer Architecture\nYEAR 4\nPart Time\n\nManagement Support Systems\nTechnical Communication\nInformation Security\nObject Oriented Programming III\nBusiness Policy and Strategy\nProfessional Issues in ICT\nSoftware Quality Assurance\nFinal Project\n\nEntry Requirement:\n\t\tFive credits at the GCE Ordinary Level including Mathematics and English\n\n\t\tThree passes for GCE Advanced Level in one attempt\n\nFees\n\n\tYear 1 : LKR 400,000\n\tYear 2 : LKR 400,000\n\tYear 3 : LKR 300,000\n\tYear 4 : LKR 300,00\n\tRegistration Fee : 5,000\n\tLibrary Fee : LKR 5,000");

